metadata.name: St. Peters House #1
metadata.description:
Large block of flats at the bottom of Jacob's Wells Road. The block took its name from the late nineteenth-century church which stood on this site until 1939. Designed by the City Architect, Nelson Meredith, in 1952. The entrance to White Hart Steps leading up into Clifton was incorporated in the building.

Location: St. Peters House, Bristol.
Date: December 2020.
Camera: Mamiya 645.
Film: Kodak Portra 400.
